# Strictons admin app — local environment template.
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values for local dev.
# Real values for preview and production live in Vercel project settings.

# ---- Supabase (RLS-enforced clients use the publishable key; service-role
#                bypasses RLS — server-side use only).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=

# ---- SendGrid (production transport for sendMagicLink).
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=
# SENDGRID_FROM=        # optional override; defaults to welcome@strictons.com
# SENDGRID_REPLY_TO=    # optional override; defaults to welcome@strictons.com

# ---- Email transport selection.
# Local dev:  unset (defaults to console — engineers click links from the
#                    terminal log)
# Preview:    leave UNSET; defaults to sendgrid. Setting explicitly is the
#             Phase 3 gotcha (Q1 clarification, Phase 4 plan).
# Production: leave UNSET; defaults to sendgrid.
# E2E only:   EMAIL_TRANSPORT=memory + E2E_MODE=1
# EMAIL_TRANSPORT=
# E2E_MODE=             # set to 1 only in Playwright runs

# ---- App URLs — used to build magic-link redirect targets and any cross-app
#                  links. Both vars must be set in BOTH apps' Vercel projects:
#                  resolveAppUrl('partners') from inside admin reads
#                  NEXT_PUBLIC_PARTNERS_URL out of the admin project's env.
# Production: NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_URL=https://admin.strictons.com
#             NEXT_PUBLIC_PARTNERS_URL=https://partners.strictons.com
# Preview:    leave NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_URL unset; resolveAppUrl('admin') falls
#             back to VERCEL_URL for in-app calls. For cross-app calls from
#             admin to partners in preview, NEXT_PUBLIC_PARTNERS_URL MUST be
#             set explicitly — VERCEL_URL is admin's URL, not partners'.
# Local dev:  NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_URL=http://localhost:3001
#             NEXT_PUBLIC_PARTNERS_URL=http://localhost:3002
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PARTNERS_URL=

# ---- Sentry — wired in Phase 4 commit 3.
# DSN is read across browser / server / edge runtimes; non-NEXT_PUBLIC_
# vars are inlined to undefined in client bundles, so the NEXT_PUBLIC_
# prefix is required for the browser init to receive a value. The DSN
# is a public credential by design (Sentry docs).
#
# Same Sentry project as partners — events from this app are tagged
# `app=admin` via initialScope so the dashboard can filter cleanly.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
